description: Sparebanken Øst operates as a savings bank in Eastern Norway. The company offers savings accounts, retirement savings, guardianship accounts, and deposit accounts; car loans, home and green mortgage loans, and framework loans, as well as refinancing services; and mortgage loans for new and used cars. It also provides vehicles, houses and contents, boats, leisure, life and health, child, travel, and disability insurance products; shares and funds trading, and investment banking services; placement and payment processing services; and online and mobile banking services. In addition, the company buys, sells, and stores cryptocurrencies; and operates, leases, and sells real estate properties. The company was founded in 1843 and is headquartered in Drammen, Norway.
